intro: Racosperma multisiliquum, commonly known as the multi-seeded racosperma, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the legume family, Fabaceae, and is characterized by its compound leaves and small, pod-like fruits. The plant typically grows in dry, sandy soils and is adapted to arid environments. Its flowers are usually pale yellow or greenish, and it produces multiple seeds within its pods. Racosperma multisiliquum is often found in open woodlands and is of interest to botanists due to its ecological and evolutionary significance.
